    "creator": "Ryousuke Nanasaki",
    "date": "2022",
    "description": "<div>The memoir of gay activist Ryousuke Nanasaki and the first religiously recognized same-sex marriage in Japan.</div><div><br /></div><div>From school crushes to awkward dating sites to finding a community, this collection of stories recounts the author\u2019s \u201cfirsts\u201d as a young gay man searching for love. Dating is never ever easy, but that goes doubly so for Ryousuke, whose journey is full of unrequited loves and many speed bumps. But perseverance and time heals all wounds, even those of the heart.</div><div><br /></div><div>This moving memoir by gay activist Ryousuke Nanasaki, following his historic life story, was originally released in Japan as a novel of collected essays. They are compiled here beautifully in a manga format.</div>",
